<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36148e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36148e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36148e"> 148(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> family budget</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[A &ldquo;Statement showing income and estimated necessary expenditure,&rdquo; or fairly detailed <mark>family budget</mark> is given]</font> A consideration of this <mark>statement of income and expenditure</mark>, and of the number of people who are living under the conditions which it indicates, remind us how precarious are the lives of the poor, who are at all times liable to be plunged into poverty by the death or illness of the chief wage-earner. <small> B. Seebohm Rowntree, <a name="BSRP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BSRP"><cite title="source">Poverty, A Study of Town Life</cite></a>, 3rd ed.? (1922) 157</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
